# Trivy ignore policy for The Copy
#
# Each entry must include CVE id, scope, and the rationale that justifies
# treating the finding as not exploitable in our runtime context. Reassess
# whenever a base image, pnpm version, or container layout changes.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# picomatch CVE-2026-33671 / CVE-2026-33672  (HIGH / MEDIUM, ReDoS)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# picomatch ships pre-bundled inside two locations that we cannot reach with a
# pnpm override:
#   1. /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/**          (npm bundled with Node 24)
#   2. /home/backenduser/.cache/node/corepack/**   (corepack-cached pnpm tarball)
#   3. /root/.cache/node/corepack/**               (builder-stage corepack cache)
#
# We do not invoke npm at runtime (the runner uses node directly via the
# entrypoint), and pnpm is only invoked by docker-entrypoint.sh for opt-in
# db:push migrations against operator-controlled inputs — never user input.
# A ReDoS in picomatch requires attacker-controlled glob input, which is not
# reachable through any path that runs against picomatch in either tool.
CVE-2026-33671
CVE-2026-33672

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# brace-expansion CVE-2026-33750  (MEDIUM, ReDoS)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Same containment rationale as picomatch above: brace-expansion is bundled by
# the same npm/corepack paths and is not invoked against any user-controlled
# string in the runtime path.
CVE-2026-33750
